@node "Overview" "ED/GED | Overview"
@{b}ED/GED@{ub} is my replacement for the  ED/GED  quickstarter  for  GoldED. Some of the
things that bothered me was:

    · It didn't put control back to the shell, even if the stick bit was not
      set.

    · It couldn't load a new configuration file if GoldED is already started.

    · It couldn't go to another screen if GoldED is already started.

    · It did not support wildcards.

so I fixed the above, and added a few more options. Now it recognizes  the file
extension and will try to load a matching preference file. Included is also a
small rexx macro, that when run from within GoldED will load the configuration
that fits the current windows extension. This macro is called "LoadConfig.ged"
@endnode

